      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD3S is a museum-grade example of Japanese engineering, featuring the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. Maintained with clinical precision, the power delivery remains linear and robust, benefiting from a complete vacuum system overhaul and verified high compression across all rotor faces. The chassis retains its factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and Torsen limited-slip differential, ensuring the 50/50 weight distribution provides the telepathic handling these icons are renowned for. Finished in original paint with a flawless interior and zero modifications, this vehicle represents a rare opportunity to own a pure, unmodified apex-predator of the 90s in concours-level condition.",
